            "body": "### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?\n\nDon't known / other\n\n### Is this a regression?\n\nYes\n\n### Description\n\nWhen an ampersand appears in an embedded expression, for example as part of a logical operator or literal, and the expression can evaluate to an HTML entity, that entity may not display properly.  E.g. <pre>{{(true && true) ? '&amp;ndash;' : '&amp;eacute;'}}</pre> results in the string \"&amp;ndash;\" being displayed.\r\n\r\nMore specifically, it appears that all characters from any ampersand to the subsequent semicolon are interpreted as if they are an entity regardless of placement, as can be seen in the reproduction:\r\n<pre>\r\n{{(true && true) ? '&amp;ndash;' : '&amp;eacute;'}} -> renders the string \"&amp;ndash;\"\r\n{{(true && ';') ? '&amp;ndash;' : '&amp;eacute;'}} -> renders &ndash; (an en dash)\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\nExamples in the reproduction follow:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/109766913/180320422-9c1a69c8-832c-46d2-90b6-ea8c1a2a330a.png)\r\n\r\nI recently upgraded from Angular 11 to 14 following the instructions.  I do not believe this existed in the earlier version, but suppose I can't be 100% positive of that.\n\n### Please provide a link to a minimal reproduction of the bug\n\nhttps://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-ivy-znh2ze\n\n### Please provide the exception or error you saw\n\n```true\nHTML entity renders as a string instead of the symbol.  No error is reported.\n```\n\n\n### Please provide the environment you discovered this bug in (run `ng version`)\n\n```true\nAngular CLI: 14.0.6\r\nNode: 14.15.1\r\nPackage Manager: npm 6.14.5\r\nOS: win32 x64\r\n\r\nAngular: 14.0.6\r\n... animations, cli, common, compiler, compiler-cli, core, forms\r\n... language-service, platform-browser, platform-browser-dynamic\r\n... platform-server, router\r\n\r\nPackage                         Version\r\n---------------------------------------------------------\r\n@angular-devkit/architect       0.1400.6\r\n@angular-devkit/build-angular   14.0.6\r\n@angular-devkit/core            14.0.6\r\n@angular-devkit/schematics      14.0.6\r\n@angular/cdk                    14.0.5\r\n@schematics/angular             14.0.6\r\nrxjs                            6.6.3\r\ntypescript                      4.7.4\n```\n\n\n### Anything else?\n\nThis is my first bug report, so let me know if I'm missing anything or if there's an easy way to know which package.  Thank you!",
